Comparing variant calling precision and sensitivity between three vendors

Overview

Here we compare the sensitivity and precision of variant detection using three different vendors: Sentieon, GATK, and DRAGEN. For each vendor, the same set of 17 samples (with the exception of Dragen - see below) was used for gVCF construction and joint-genotyping. The 17 samples included 16 samples from the lot 16-20 vantage run and a PCR-free bulk sample that has been subsampled to 450 million reads.
